  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n> Uncomment only one, leave it on its own line: \r\n>\r\n/kind bug\r\n> /kind feature\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nThe version of go-yaml (53feefa2559fb8dfa8d81baad31be332c97d6c77) vendored by kubernetes has this bug: https://github.com/go-yaml/yaml/issues/75\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nIf KUBECONFIG uses the exclamation mark syntax, for example:\r\n```\r\nexpiry-key: ! '{.credential.token_expiry}'\r\n```\r\nkubectl will fail to parse it.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nIt was fixed in go-yaml here: https://github.com/go-yaml/yaml/commit/670d4cfef0544295bc27a114dbac37980d83185a\r\n\r\nI'll be happy to contribute a fix, but I'd like to know if it will be accepted.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
